<subSubSection id="02C66578FFF9FFB8FF3D9DDD687B7F12" pageId="20" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFF9FFB8FF3D9DDD68567C93" blockId="20.[151,756,409,628]" pageId="20" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF9FFB8FF3D9DDD68057CD0" bold="true" box="[151,264,409,433]" pageId="20" pageNumber="34">Remarks:</emphasis>
It is distinguished by having elongate chambers and ten well developed costae that extend across the sutures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFF9FFB8FF3D9DBE687B7F12" blockId="20.[151,756,409,628]" pageId="20" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF9FFB8FF3D9DBE68C67F73" bold="true" box="[151,459,506,530]" pageId="20" pageNumber="34">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded in the Esna Shale by LE ROY (1953) and SAID &amp; KENAWY (1956). It is found in the Maastrichtian and Paleocene zones of the Esh El Mallaha area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
